                    "value": "The source workbook is a catalog of ~10 techniques Tableau users employ to fake a 3rd, 4th, 5th or 6th axis: stacking identical measures on Rows/Columns, pinning constant axis-anchor placeholders (MAX(1.0)/MAX(0.0)/0), and layering unicode shape/glyph marks driven by table calcs.",
